PUSD ITS HelpDesk
August 26 at 6:45 PM ·

UPDATE: We're back as of 6:00 a.m. Thank you for your patience!

The district internet connection is currently down. Access to on-premises services such as our information systems and email is temporarily unavailable. We've contacted our provider and will have an update soon. Any internet services not hosted by PUSD such as Zoom and Google should continue to function at home as expected.
text:
Important update from our PUSD ITS HelpDesk

PUSD ITS HelpDesk
August 26 at 6:45 PM ·

UPDATE: We're back as of 6:00 a.m. Thank you for your patience!

The district internet connection is currently down. Access to on-premises services such as our information systems and email is temporarily unavailable. We've contacted our provider and will have an update soon. Any internet services not hosted by PUSD such as Zoom and Google should continue to function at home as expected.

I was privileged to help Decker Elementary School (Pomona California) last week by supplying copies of the Distance Learning Handbook (Corwin Publishing) to help their faculty. Thank you Principal Rebecca Norwood for this opportunity to help.

I purchased two extra copies of this book that I will raffle on Facebook Live this Friday (8/28) at 3 pm. Teachers, if you want to enter this free raffle, please like, comment on and share this post (all 3). HAve a great week everyone and please stay safe! #politoagency

July 8 at 9:06 AM ·

Staff is reporting issues signing into Zoom with the Chrome browser ever since the trial expired on 7/1. Zoom has graciously extended our trial another 10 days while we implement our licensed version. If anyone is having issues signing into Zoom with their apps.pusd.org account, simply clear your cache and cookies in the browser settings.

Contact your ITS Helpdesk for assistance.

shared_text:
Renee Barbee is feeling proud at Ganesha High School Giants.
June 4 at 9:05 PM · Pomona, CA ·

Last week I covered Ganesha High School 's #poseandpass for Pomona Unified School District

It was so awesome to see the #seniors in their 🎓 & #gown - wearing proudly as each gal & guy represents the #graduatingclassof2020

The lady dressed in black with a 📢📣 was explaining to students & their family members what they needed to do for #socialdistancing 😷

It was slightly overcast that day so I spent most of this evening making the photos brighter for clarity.

One little boy was trying to pop the streamer but was having trouble so a very nice man came over to help. Simply adorable.

Congratulations to the seniors - graduating class of 2020. 🎓👏👏👏👍🎉🎈🙂💙🤎🖤🤍🙏🎁✨☀️🌥️🦋🎤🎶‼️🇱🇷

We are working on a plan toward the reopening of our schools under the direction from our state officials, county public health officials, and education officials. We will follow the Los Angeles County Department of Public Health guidelines for Social Distancing and Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) to ensure maximum safety in light of COVID-19. We would like to get information from you as we adapt to the best instructional program for the 2020-21 school year.

Please take a few minutes to share your thoughts in this brief and anonymous survey. Your name and/or child’s name will not be required. (Please fill out a separate survey for each child.)

According to his students, Mr. Crockett is the real deal @diamondranchhighschool ! His students admire his knowledge and passion for his subject and his dedication to making sure they have accurate information and resources to pursue their love of art. They appreciate how he puts the arts in perspective and how the arts play a role in our society and culture. The invitation to philosophical conversation and challenging concepts are explored in contemporary and classical exchanges. Creative problem solving through the arts help students rise in other subjects ! Thank you Mr. Crockett for inspiring the creative and inquiring minds in your visual arts class. #artteachersofinstagram #teacherappreciationweek #dapomona #PUSD

Countless students have been enlightened in Sadigheh Phillips Village Academy’s visual arts class. Sadigheh has a gift to direct and engage her students in classic studio arts studies to the digital age. She has faithfully worked with her students to design the Annual Emerging Artists exhibition every May and she always encouraged the students and families to attend the special art opening. She cares deeply about her students and fortifies them will skills they can rely on the rest of their lives. Thank you Sadigheh ! #teacherappreciationweek #teachersofinstagram #dapomona #pomonavibes #pusd

Countless students have been enlightened in Sadigheh Phillips Village Academy’s visual arts class. Sadigheh has a gift to direct and engage her students in classic studio arts studies to the digital age. She has faithfully worked with her students to design the Annual Emerging Artists exhibition every May and she always encouraged the students and families to attend the special art opening. She cares deeply about her students and fortifies them will skills they can rely on the rest of their lives. dAPomona would like feature our own Vicki Tessier as she defines DEDICATION ! She coordinates all of the PUSD visual arts, music, dance classes and provides the teachers with guidelines for planning, delivering, and assessing a comprehensive arts education program for all students pre-K-12 !
Every May Vickie makes her rounds to each school to collect the student’s artwork and then carefully installs the art, and magically prepares an amazing awards reception for the students and their families at dAPomona !
Vickie is passionate about every student in PUSD having access to the ARTS and we are in awe of how one person accomplishes !!!! KUDOS VICKIE ! Thank you for all you do !

* No Walk-ins will be allowed for the safety of everyone.

This form is to support technology issues during school closures. If staff or students need a charger or device, please fill out this form completely. If you have a device but need tech support please call (909) 397-4800 ext. 23780. If you select a designated appointment time to pick-up a device or charger, you are confirmed for that time unless you receive a phone call otherwise. For example hotspots and teacher laptops will need to be confirmed, as supplies are limited.

Student & Staff Device Support - Drive Thru Service
* No Walk-ins will be allowed for the safety of everyone.

This form is to support technology issues during school closures. If staff or students need a charger or device, please fill out this form completely. If you have a device but need tech support please call (909) 397-4800 ext. 23780. If you select a designated appointment time to pick-up a device or charger, you are confirmed for that time unless you receive a phone call otherwise. For example hotspots and teacher laptops will need to be confirmed, as supplies are limited.
